{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 What this edition includes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Tiling Shell GNOME extension (bundled)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 win11-tiling-setup} command for one-step installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab GNOME-only \u8212- no KDE or X11 fallback components\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Upstream project\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Tiling Shell: https://github.com/domferr/tilingshell\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 2. Requirements\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Fedora Workstation} (GNOME edition)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b GNOME Shell 45 or newer} (Fedora 41+)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Packages installed automatically with the RPM:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\f1 gnome-shell}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\f1 gnome-extensions}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\f1 unzip}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\f1 dbus}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\f1 bash}\sa180\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 To check your GNOME version:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 gnome-shell --version\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 3. Installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Step 1 \u8212- Copy the RPM to your Fedora machine\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Transfer the file:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\f1 win11-window-tiling-1.0.0-1.fc41.noarch.rpm}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Step 2 \u8212- Install with dnf\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Open a terminal in the folder containing the RPM, then run:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 sudo dnf install ./win11-window-tiling-1.0.0-1.fc41.noarch.rpm\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\f1 dnf} resolves and installs required dependencies ({\f1 gnome-shell}, {\f1 gnome-extensions}, etc.) automatically.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Step 3 \u8212- Verify installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 rpm -q win11-window-tiling\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Expected output: {\f1 win11-window-tiling-1.0.0-1.fc41.noarch}\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 4. First-Time Setup\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Run setup\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 win11-tiling-setup\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This command:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Detects your GNOME Shell version\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Installs the Tiling Shell extension to your user profile\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Enables the extension (if {\f1 gnome-extensions} is available)\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Log out and back in\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 GNOME Shell extensions require a fresh session. Log out completely, then sign back in (a reboot also works).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Verify\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 win11-tiling-setup --status\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Example output:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 Edition:          Fedora Workstation (GNOME)\line
Session type:     wayland\line
Setup status:     configured (2026-06-28T...)\line
GNOME extension:  installed\line
Name:             Tiling Shell\line
State:            ENABLED\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Also open {\b Extensions} (search Activities for \u8220"Extensions\u8221") and confirm {\b Tiling Shell} is toggled {\b ON}.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
